Absolutely — here’s a clean, self-contained HTML “clone” of that slice (from “In my 16 years of teaching …” through “…solidified it with a proven process”, including the 4 boxes). I’ve **removed the duplicated “Solutions” block** that appears on the live page so you can edit once and ship fast. Everything is in one file; just paste into your editor and tweak copy inside the obvious `<h*>`/`<p>` tags.

> Source mapping (for your reference): “In my 16 years… + 3 Challenges” citeturn1view0; “Solutions 1–3” (first occurrence) citeturn1view0; “...solidified it with a proven process (4 steps)” citeturn1view0

```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Promo Section — Challenges → Solutions → 4-Step Process</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #ffffff;
      --ink: #111827;
      --muted: #4b5563;
      --accent: #0ea5e9;  /* tweak as needed */
      --card: #f9fafb;
      --ring: rgba(14,165,233,0.3);
      --radius: 14px;
      --gap: 18px;
      --maxw: 1120px;
    }
    body { margin: 0; font: 16px/1.6 system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; color: var(--ink); background: var(--bg); }
    .wrap { max-width: var(--maxw); margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 20px; }
    .eyebrow { text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; font-weight: 700; font-size: 12px; color: var(--accent); }
    h2 { margin: 8px 0 10px; font-size: clamp(24px, 4vw, 36px); line-height: 1.2; }
    h3 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: clamp(18px, 2.6vw, 22px); line-height: 1.3; }
    h4 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: clamp(16px, 2.2vw, 20px); }
    p.lead { color: var(--muted); margin: 8px 0 22px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .grid { display: grid; gap: var(--gap); }
    .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0,1fr)); }
    .grid-4 { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0,1fr)); }
    @media (max-width: 980px) { .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } .grid-4 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
    @media (max-width: 640px) { .grid-3, .grid-4 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    .card, .step {
      background: var(--card);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 18px 16px;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.03);
    }
    .card p, .step p { margin: 6px 0 0; color: var(--muted); }
    .step .kicker {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      width: 34px; height: 34px; border-radius: 10px; font-weight: 700;
      background: var(--accent); color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px var(--ring);
    }
    .section { margin: 36px 0 8px; }
    .divider { height: 1px; background: #e5e7eb; margin: 28px 0; }
    /* utility for quick emphasis */
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="wrap">

    <!-- =====================  CHALLENGES  ===================== -->
    <section aria-labelledby="challenges">
      <div class="eyebrow">Why students plateau</div>
      <h2 id="challenges">In my 16 years of teaching, I’ve observed three recurring blockers</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Even strong Upper-Sec and JC students can stall short of top grades. These are the patterns I see most often:
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-3" role="list">
        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Challenge 1: Mastering the Basics</h3>
          <p>Small gaps in fundamentals compound. Without a firm base, every new topic feels harder than it should.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Challenge 2: Learning Approach</h3>
          <p>Large, one-pace-fits-all classes rarely adapt to an individual’s needs, so misconceptions linger.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Challenge 3: Classroom Environment</h3>
          <p>Fast pace and competitive settings can inhibit questions, leading to hidden misunderstandings.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider" role="presentation"></div>

    <!-- =====================  SOLUTIONS  ===================== -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="solutions">
      <div class="eyebrow">What we change</div>
      <h2 id="solutions">So, I created an approach that directly addresses these blockers</h2>
      <p class="lead">This isn’t just “exam prep” — it builds durable understanding that carries into future study.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-3" role="list">
        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Solution 1: An Expert Tutor</h3>
          <p>Deep subject mastery + long experience → clear explanations, precise diagnosis, real confidence.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Solution 2: Personalised &amp; Guided</h3>
          <p>Plans tailored to each student’s profile; difficult topics finally “click” through targeted practice.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card" role="listitem">
          <h3>Solution 3: Supportive &amp; Confidential</h3>
          <p>A safe space to ask, try, and iterate — progress measured against the student’s own baseline.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider" role="presentation"></div>

    <!-- =====================  PROVEN PROCESS (4 BOXES)  ===================== -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="process">
      <div class="eyebrow">How we execute</div>
      <h2 id="process">…and solidified it with a proven process</h2>
      <p class="lead">Your path to mastery in four focused steps.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-4" role="list" aria-label="Four-step process">
        <article class="step" role="listitem">
          <div class="kicker" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
          <h4>Discovery</h4>
          <p>Initial sessions surface strengths, gaps, and habits. We align goals and measurement upfront.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="step" role="listitem">
          <div class="kicker" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
          <h4>Custom-Built Lessons</h4>
          <p>We target weak points with sequenced practice to notch quick wins and build momentum.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="step" role="listitem">
          <div class="kicker" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
          <h4>Guided Mastery Sessions</h4>
          <p>Concepts are consolidated through coached problem-solving until understanding is complete.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="step" role="listitem">
          <div class="kicker" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
          <h4>Lock In the Knowledge</h4>
          <p>Spiral review and exam-style application cement recall and exam-day performance.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</body>
</html>
```

